bishop in the united states died thursday at the age of 96 
furlong was ordained in 1918 he became president of cathedral 
college in 1938 and held that post until 1941 
in 1941 furlong was named monsignor with the title of papal 
chamberlain in 1945 he was named a domestic prelate and was made 
secretary of education for the archdiocese of new york 
five years later he became pastor of st thomas more parish in 
manhattan and was elevated to prothonotary apostolic in 1956 he 
