hu yaobang an outspoken reformer who led the 
worlds largest communist party until a 1987 purge consigned him to 
political oblivion died of heart failure saturday he was 73 
the protege of senior leader deng xiaoping died one week after 
he suffered a heart attack during a meeting of the politburo the 
ruling body that dismissed him as party general secretary two years 
before 
at beijing university hundreds of students put up posters 
praising hu as a reformer and indirectly criticizing those who 
ousted him 
the chinese communist party he led for seven years described hu 
as a great proletarian revolutionary and loyal communist 
fighter who led a glorious life with everlasting merits for the 
party and the people 
but hu suffered from his partys swift ideological shifts 
he joined mao tsetung on the 193435 long march but was 
targeted by maos red guards during the 196676 cultural 
revolution spending nearly the entire decade banished to the 
countryside or under house arrest 
hus political fortunes rose after maos death and he helped 
revive chinas economy through marketoriented reforms he once 
stood on the threshold of succeeding deng xiaoping as the leader of 
chinas 11 billion people but he fell from grace over 1986 
prodemocracy student demonstrations 
he was forced to resign on jan 16 1987 after being blamed for 
failing to put down the demonstrations hu who had reportedly 
alienated deng with his outspoken manner also was accused of 
promoting dangerously high growth rates and neglecting to stop the 
trend toward westernization 
hu retained his seat on the powerful 17member politburo but he 
made no public statements and appeared ill at ease in his few 
public appearances 
he was last seen during the annual session of chinas 
parliament the national peoples congress which ended april 4 
at beijing university saturday hundreds of students milled 
around posters praising hu as a leading force in reform one 
poster referred obliquely to hus 1987 ouster as that year when 
you were made to play the scapegoat 
may your spirit reawaken to bear witness to history 
another poster said in an apparent call for a review of the 
charges against him 
the evening television news briefly played mournful music while 
displaying a picture of hu then read a communist party statement 
that praised hu as a statesman and great proletarian 
revolutionary 
the statement did not mention hus ouster in disgrace 
the chainsmoking hu dengs longtime bridge partner was widely 
expected to take over dengs functions when chinas senior leader 
now 84 stepped down 
the unofficial scenario called for hu once he overcame the 
suspicions of the conservative military to take over dengs posts 
and become the nations undisputed leader instead former premier 
zhao ziyang succeeded hu as party boss and li peng who favors 
economic stability over reform initiatives became premier 
hu was born in november 1915 in liuyang county hunan province 
according to official reports he left home at the age of 14 to 
join the communist party childrens corps 
he took part in the long march the red armys epic flight from 
chiang kaisheks nationalist forces and served as a political 
commissar during the 193745 war against japan 
hu became secretary of the communist youth league in 1952 three 
years after maos forces took over the mainland and in 1956 he was 
appointed to the party central committee 
in 1966 as head of the youth league he became a prime target 
of maos cultural revolution red guards shaved his head forced 
him to crawl on his hands and knees and exiled him to rural henan 
province 
among his alleged crimes was that he and deng another victim of 
the leftists used railroad cars and special airplanes to ferry 
bridge partners around the country 
hu was rehabilitated in 1977 and headed the party office in 
charge of redressing injustice during the cultural revolution 
he quickly rankled party ideologues men who would later push 
for his ouster by criticizing mao for his role in the cultural 
revolution which he described as a period of catastrophe in 
which nothing was correct or positive 
he was elected secretary general of the party central committee 
in 1980 and served as chairman of the party from june 1981 until 
the title was abolished in september 1982 he then became general 
secretary of the party 
hu had four children and five grandchildren his wife li zhao is 
a clothing designer and former official in the beijing textile 
bureau 
