colombian president virgilio barco says the 
only way to battle drug trafficking successfully is if all the 
countries of the americas join together in the fight 
drug production consumption and traffic is not a problem of 
one nation not even of a group of nations barco told the 
american societ of newspaper editors on friday it is a universal 
scourge we cannot expect successful results if colombia or 
for that matter any country is left to act alone 
barco said the scourge could not be ended until the united 
states which consumes more than half the worlds supply of 
cocaine reduces its demand for the drug and he called for a 
summit of the presidents of the americas to focus on the problem 
the insatiable demand for drugs in this country is also the 
greatest single threat to democracy in our hemisphere barco said 
the only law narcotics traffic does not break is the economic 
law of supply and demand he said if cocaine sales are 
tolerated on your streets coca will continue to be grown in the 
hidden valleys and hillsides of south america we can only break 
this trail through concerted action at both ends 
among the summit topics he said would be the sharing of police 
intelligence and satellite information better interdiction both of 
drugs and of chemicals needed to make those drugs better transport 
and equipment for law enforcement agencies and more support for 
